body:
@cowtowncoder reproducer:

```java
    public static void main(String[] args) throws JsonProcessingException {
        ObjectMapper objectMapper = new ObjectMapper();
        objectMapper.enable(SerializationFeature.WRAP_ROOT_VALUE);

        Event value = new Event();
        value.id = 1L;
        value.name = "foo";
        System.out.println(objectMapper.writeValueAsString(value)); // {"event":{"id":1,"name":"foo"}}
        System.out.println(objectMapper.valueToTree(value)); // {"id":1,"name":"foo"}
    }

    @JsonRootName("event")
    public static class Event {
        public Long id;
        public String name;
    }
```

The bug was introduced in 2e986dfe5937b28ba39b4d28e0f993802c7c9f68 because valueToTree now explicitly drops WRAP_ROOT_VALUE. imo this should be reverted
